The Bungoma government has spent Sh36 million to rehabilitated Chwele market &ndash; the second largest open-air bazaar in East Africa.On Wednesday, Governor Kenneth Lusaka said the county will build a bus park and fix the drainage system.&ldquo;We want this market to have a good look. My administration is keen in developing it to ensure Bungoma becomes a 24-hour town,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;People come from all corners of East Africa to do business here, but its standards are poor. We need tochange this.&rdquo;